Steps to follow:
01 - ./OS_Install

02 - ./Headless_BasicSetup

03 - Login, Update, Upgrade, Git and Change password in RaspberryPi, and hostname:
      Login:
        ssh pi@IP_address

      Update and Upgrade:
        sudo apt-get update
        sudo apt-get upgrade

      Install Git:
        sudo apt-get install git

      Change password:
        passwd (default password is 'raspberry')

      Change hostname 'raspberry' to 'gitpi'
        sudo nano /etc/hostname
        sudo nano /etc/hosts

        exit

04 - ./SSHPasswordless_Setup

05 - Linux/Git/GitUserSetup

06 - Login as git user to Gitpi server, and create repository:
      New project:
        git init --bare project.git

      Existing project:
        git clone --bare project project.git

      This step is to make sure the owner of the repository is user 'git'

07 - Login as 'pi' (sudoer) user to Gitpi server, and mv previously created
     repository to /srv/git:
      If not already created /srv/git:
        sudo mkdir /srv/git

      Move Repository:
        sudo mv /home/git/project.git /srv/git